<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
      		
      		<p n="1">
      			<supplied reason="undefined">Fortune!</supplied>
      		</p>
      		
      		<p n="1-2">
      			Ninth year of the victorious king Paramēccuvaraparumaṉ.<note>Sanskrit Parameśvaravarman.</note>
      		</p>
      		
      		<p n="3-8">
      			Mukaṉ<!--Update:add markup for translation unclear, tentative-->, the son <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Pāratāyar, the lord of Mēṟceṅkai<note>Alternatively, simply "Pāratāyar of Mēṟceṅkai".</note><!--Update: translate: māmm. Part of the placename-->, fell recovering cattle, when <supplied reason="undefined">Va</supplied>miṟaiyār<!--Update:add markup for translation unclear, tentative-->, a temple dignitary <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kōyil paṭṭar</foreign></supplied> in Iḷakkōvūrnāṭu in Vēṇāṭu, came and seized cattle.
      			 
      		</p>      		
      		
